						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Advancing-Agriculture-in-Developing-Countries-through-Knowledge-and-Innovation-Synopsis-of-an-International-Conference" title="Advancing Agriculture in Developing Countries through Knowledge and Innovation Synopsis of an International Conference" alt="link">Advancing Agriculture in Developing Countries through Knowledge and Innovation Synopsis of an International Conference</a></h2>

	
					<p>By Kwadwo Asenso-Okyere, Kristin Davis, and Dejene Aredo, IFPRI, November 2008. This document is a synopsis of the conference presentations and discussions on ideas and experiences relating to knowledge and innovation among different innovation agents (including public, private, and civil sectors). The synopsis is one of a number of conference outputs and is intended to provide a concise overview of the outcomes. Topics dealt with include (a) the role of knowledge and innovation in meeting the challenges of reducing poverty in developing countries, (b) the roles different actors play in agricultural development and poverty reduction, and (c) whether new and appropriate technologies and policies are available for the purpose of reducing rural poverty. </p>
							<p><span class="date">2/12/2008</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Advancing-Agriculture-in-Developing-Countries-through-Knowledge-and-Innovation-Synopsis-of-an-International-Conference">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
