						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/How-can-African-Agriculture-Adapt-to-Climate-Change-Insights-from-Ethiopia-and-South-Africa" title="How can African Agriculture Adapt to Climate Change? Insights from Ethiopia and South Africa" alt="link">How can African Agriculture Adapt to Climate Change? Insights from Ethiopia and South Africa</a></h2>

	
					<p>20 Briefs, IFPRI, October 2008. This series of IFPRI Research Briefs is based on research supported by the Federal Ministry for Economic Cooperation and Development, Germany, under the project &quot;Food and Water Security under Global Change: Developing Adaptive Capacity with a Focus on Rural Africa”. The project aims to provide policymakers and stakeholders in Ethiopia and South Africa with tools to better understand and analyze the consequences of global change—in particular climate change—and to form policy decisions that facilitate adaptation in these countries and beyond.</p>
							<p><span class="date">2/12/2008</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/How-can-African-Agriculture-Adapt-to-Climate-Change-Insights-from-Ethiopia-and-South-Africa">Read more...</a>
